          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Cylindrical target chamber made of Sol-Gel coated",
                "Pyrex glass 39.6 cm long and 2.9 cm in diameter was",
                "connected to spherical pumping chamber 8.1 cm. The",
                "spin-exchange optical pumping technique was used to",
                "polarize 3He target. A small quantity of Rb and K was",
                "placed in the pumping chamber, heated to 196 deg C. A",
                "circularly polarized 794.8 nm laser light incident on",
                "the pumping chamber polarized Rb atoms which in turn",
                "transferred their polarization to 3He. The target was",
                "filled with (6.5+-0.1) amg of 3He.",
                " (1 amg = 44.615 mol/m3)",
                "Polarization of the target was 33% for the initial run",
                "period and 22% for the final run period."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Protons from the 3He photodisintegrations",
                "were detected by 72 fully depleted silicon surface",
                "barrier detectors. The detectors were placed at the",
                "proton angles of 45, 70, 95, and 120 deg (18",
                "detectors at each angle) along the target at a",
                "distance of 10 cm from target axis."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two BC-501A liquid scintillator detectors were",
                "used to detect neutrons from the deuteron",
                "photodisintegration process to monitor photon flux."
              ]
            }
          ],
